4 A BILL FOR AN ACT ENTITLED: “AN ACT REVISING ALCOHOL LICENSES TO PROHIBIT THE
5 DEPARTMENT OF REVENUE FROM DENYING A TRANSFER OF AN ALCOHOL LICENSE SOLELY
6 BECAUSE THE SELLER HAS OUTSTANDING TAXES, PENALTIES, OR INTEREST OWED TO THE
7 DEPARTMENT; PROVIDING THAT PROCEEDS FROM THE SALE OF THE ALCOHOL LICENSE MAY GO
8 TO ANY OUTSTANDING LIENS OWED TO THE DEPARTMENT; AMENDING SECTIONS 16-4-404 AND 16-
9 6-303, MCA; AND PROVIDING AN IMMEDIATE EFFECTIVE DATE AND AN APPLICABILITY DATE.”
10
11 BE IT ENACTED BY THE LEGISLATURE OF THE STATE OF MONTANA:
12
13 Section 1. Section 16-4-404, MCA, is amended to read:
14 "16-4-404. Protest period -- contents of license -- posting -- privilege -- transfer. (1) A license
15 may not be issued until on or after the date set in the notice for hearing protests.
16 (2) Every license issued under this code must state the name of the person to whom it is issued,
17 the location, by street and number or other appropriate specific description of location if no street address
18 exists, of the premises where the business is to be carried on under the license, and other information the
19 department considers necessary. If the licensee is a partnership or if more than one person has an interest in
20 the business operated under the license, the names of all persons in the partnership or interested in the
21 business must appear on the license. Every license must be posted in a conspicuous place on the premises in
22 which the business authorized under the license is conducted, and the license must be exhibited on request to
23 any authorized representative of the department or the department of justice or to any peace officer of the state
24 of Montana.
25 (3) A license issued under the provisions of this code is a privilege personal to the licensee named
26 in the license and is valid until the expiration of the license unless sooner revoked or suspended.
27 (4) A license may be transferred pursuant to 16-4-431 to the personal representative, executor, or
28 administrator of the estate of a deceased licensee, or to a designee of the personal representative, executor, or
