1 administrator, when the estate consists in whole or in part of the business of selling alcoholic beverages under
2 a license. The license may descend or be disposed of with the licensed business under appropriate probate
3 proceedings.
4 (5) A licensee may apply to the department for a transfer of the license to different premises within
5 the quota area. The department may, after notice and opportunity for protest, permit a transfer if the transfer is
6 justified by public convenience and necessity, pursuant to 16-4-203, unless a public convenience and necessity
7 hearing is required by 16-4-207.
8 (6) On a bona fide sale of the business operated under a license, the license may be transferred to
9 a qualified purchaser. A transfer of a license to a person or location is not effective unless approved by the
10 department. A licensee or transferee or proposed transferee who operates or attempts to operate under a
11 supposedly transferred license prior to the approval of the transfer by the department, endorsed on the license
12 in writing, is considered to be operating without a license and the license affected may be revoked or
13 suspended by the department.
14 (7) The department may not deny or withhold approval of the transfer of an alcoholic beverage
15 license to a purchaser or transferee solely because of outstanding taxes, penalties, or interest owed by the
16 seller. Any proceeds from the sale of an alcoholic beverage license are subject to any existing liens or warrants
17 for distraint that the department has filed against the seller as provided in 16-1-414.
18 (8) The alcoholic beverage inventory of an existing licensee may be transferred under the following
19 scenarios:
20 (a) on a bona fide sale of the business operated under a license when the department:
21 (i) has granted temporary operating authority to the buyer to operate the license; or
22 (ii) has approved transfer of the license to the buyer;
23 (b) on a license type change at an existing licensed premises when the department has granted
24 temporary operating authority or approved the issuance of the new license, as long as the alcoholic beverage is
25 allowed by the new license type;
26 (c) on approval of a corporate structure change at an existing licensed premises;
27 (d) on the sale of a license to be floated out of a quota area when the department has granted
28 temporary operating authority or approved the license transfer; or
