1 (e) when a licensee is going out of business but only if the unopened alcohol is in its original
2 packaging and the licensee receiving the alcohol is licensed for that type of alcohol.
3 (9) Except as provided in 16-4-204 and subsections (2) through (7) (8) of this section, a license
4 may not be transferred or sold or used for any place of business not described in the license. A license may be
5 subject to mortgage and other valid liens, in which event the name of the mortgagee, on application to and
6 approval of the department, must be endorsed on the license. Beer or wine sold to a licensee on credit
7 pursuant to 16-3-243 or 16-3-406 does not create a lien on a license, but a subsequent licensee has the
