10 Section 2. Section 16-6-303, MCA, is amended to read:
11 "16-6-303. Sale of liquor not purchased or transferred from agency liquor store forbidden --
12 penalty. It is unlawful for any licensee to sell or keep for sale or have on the licensee's premises for any
13 purpose any liquor except that purchased from an agency liquor store or transferred as allowed in 16-4-404(7)
14 (8). Any licensee found in possession of or selling and keeping for sale any liquor that was not purchased from
15 an agency liquor store or transferred as allowed in 16-4-404(7) (8) shall, upon conviction, be punished by a fine
16 of not less than $500 or more than $1,500, by imprisonment for not less than 3 months or more than 1 year, or
17 by both fine and imprisonment. If the department is satisfied that the liquor was knowingly sold or kept for sale
18 within the licensed premises by the licensee or by the licensee's agents, servants, or employees, the
19 department shall immediately revoke the license."
20
21 NEW SECTION. Section 3. Effective date. [This act] is effective on passage and approval.
22
23 NEW SECTION. Section 4. Applicability. [This act] applies to all alcohol license transfers:
24 (1) filed with the department before [the effective date of this act] and that are being considered by
25 the department as of [the effective date of this act]; or
26 (2) filed with the department on or after [the effective date of this act].
27 - END -
